A district in Moldova. Holercani, Marcauti, Molovata, Oxentea, and Ustia are situated on the western (right) bank of the river Dniester, while the other 10 - on the eastern bank, of which six (Cocieri, Vasilievca, Corjova, Mahala, Molovata Noua, and Roghi) - north of the city of Dubasari, itself under the control of the separatist authorities of Transnistria, and the remaining four -south of the city. The village of Vasilievca, as well as considerable parts of the farmland of the villages of Cocieri, Roghi, and Dorotcaia are situated east of the Tiraspol-Dubasari-Rabnita road.
